"StrictHostKeyChecking" is a flag in the ssh config file.

It can be set to:

yes
no
ask
ask-no
ask-yes

The default is:

no

If set to "yes", then the ssh command will fail if the host key is not present in the local known_hosts file.

If set to "no", then the ssh command will automatically add the host key to the local known_hosts file.

